  "_layoutNotes": [
    "Layout derived 2026-05-27 from Happy_Birthday___Piano.mid (uploaded by Han).",
    "9 measures of 3/4. m0 = anacrusis (silent beats 1+2, 'Hap-py' on beat 3 dotted-eighth + sixteenth).",
    "m1: Birth-day to (3 quarters). m2: 'you,' (half) + Hap-py anacrusis line 2 (beat 3).",
    "m3: line 2 melody. m4: 'you,' + anacrusis line 3. m5: 'Birth-day dear' (line 3).",
    "m6: '[name]' + anacrusis line 4 (incl. one continuation onset on hard). m7: line 4 melody.",
    "m8: 'you!' final (dotted-half).",
    "MIDI source was in G major 4/4; reinterpreted as 3/4. Lines 1-3 end with 'you' as half-note then anacrusis-in-same-measure (per MIDI). Line 4 ends with 'you!' as dotted-half.",
    "Fermata on '[name]' (offset 216) is NOT yet encoded — fermata feature is on BACKLOG. For easy, [name] duration is stretched to 24 (half-note) to approximate the fermata feel.",
    "[Claude 2026-06-15] The line above is now OUTDATED: the fermata IS encoded — each difficulty carries a `fermatas:[{tick:216,hold:18}]` array (kept for the historical record per agent rules §4; flag to Han before deleting).",
    "[Claude 2026-06-15] Difficulty restructure (Han 1A): EASY now provides ALL staves — treble + a simple bass (chord ROOT on beat 1 only, resting through the m0 pickup, starting at the m1 downbeat) + a 3/4 waltz percussion (kick on beat 1, closed hi-hat on beats 2 & 3, m1–m8) + the existing easy chords. MEDIUM is NEW: treble + bass copied verbatim from the (former) HARD chorale arrangement, NO provided chords/percussion. HARD now provides treble + chords only (its bass moved to MEDIUM). Path B (generate missing staves from chords/melody on load) is future work."
  ],
